page.title: 19BREAN DOWN PART 2
page.content: TODAY NOBODY LIVES ON THE DOWN, ALTHOUGH HOUSES NOT STANDING TODAY HAVE BEEN BUILT. IN GEOGRAPHICAL TERMS BREAN DOWN IS THE WESTERN ONSHORE EXTREMITY OFF THE MENDIPS.THE LITHOLOGY IS DOMINANTLY LIMESTONE AND FREQUENT FOSSILS FOUND IN IT HAVE DATED IT BACK TO THE CARBONIFEROUS PERIOD.FEATURES FOUND ON THE DOWN APART FROM THE CLIFF FACE INCLUED,A BLOW HOLE,NARROW INLETS AND CAVES.THE CAVES ARE MOSTLY INACCESSIBLE TO CAVERS.THE HIGHEST POINT ON THE DOWN IS 320FT AND IS SURMOUNTED BY A TRIANGULATION SURVEY POINT.ON THE SOUTH FACE OF THE DOWN STANDS A CLIFF OF RED SANDSTONE.
